OL,6,FCurwen admitted the ADRV but stated
OL,7,Fthat he had no significant fault or
OL,8,Fnegligence. The matter was then heard
OL,9,Fby the National Anti-Doping Panel
OL,10,F(NADP).
OL,12,FThe NADP tribunal concluded that,
OL,13,Fwhile Mr Curwen's ADRVs were not
OL,14,F'intentional', he was at fault and
OL,15,Facted negligently in circumstances
OL,16,Fwhere he failed to take steps to
OL,17,Finvestigate whether his medication
OL,18,Fincluded a Prohibited Substance or to
OL,19,Fobtain a TUE prior to taking it.
